The Smile Week initiative kicked off at the Cape facility on Monday. CAPE TOWN – Forty young burn victims are set to undergo reconstructive surgery the Red Cross War Memorial Hospital this week. The Smile Week initiative kicked off at the Cape facility on Monday. Experts say that fluid burns account for more than 80% of burn injuries to South African children. Smile Foundation CEO Hedley Lewis says: “South Africa is really an unbelievable country and it’s a privilege that the Smile Foundation is partnering with these hospitals to change children’s lives.”